Clayton Dubilier & Rice Makes $415 Million Investment in Personal-Care Products
Acquisition of High Ridge Brands includes Zest soap, VO5 hair care products  

 






By

Sharon Terlep


Sharon Terlep
The Wall Street Journal
BiographySharon Terlep
@sharonterlep





  May 16, 2016 4:56 p.m. ET





Private-equity firm Clayton Dubilier & Rice LLC is making a bet on Zest soap. The private-equity shop, which owns David’s Bridal and lawn-care company TruGreen, has agreed to pay $415 million for High Ridge Brands, a personal-care products company that includes Zest, Alberto VO5 hair products and White Rain shampoos, according to private-equity firm Brynwood Partners, the seller. The sale will be announced Tuesday. High...
  


